The victory has been hailed as a testament to her exceptional athleticism and determination, with Faulkner not initially expected to secure a spot on the Olympic team.

name: Jade Carey
summary: Jade Carey, an Oregon State standout, contributed to Team USA's team gold medal at the Paris Olympics. Despite an unfortunate fall during her floor routine, Carey later redeemed herself, earning a bronze medal in the vault final, capping off her Olympic journey with a satisfying conclusion. Despite feeling unwell during the games, Carey persisted and earned a spot on the podium. Her triumph serves as a symbol of resilience and vindication, signaling the ongoing success of USA gymnasts on their Olympic redemption tour.

name: Women's vault final
summary: Simone Biles once again dominated the Women's Vault Finals at the 2024 Paris Olympics, securing her third gold medal of the Games. Despite facing the notorious "twisties" during previous competitions, Biles demonstrated her resilience, successfully landing the vault named after her. Biles' victory marks her seventh Olympic gold medal and solidifies her legacy as the most decorated American gymnast in history. Notably, Team USA earned three medals in the vault final, with Jade Carey taking silver and MyKayla Skinner claiming bronze. The competition was closely followed, with NBC providing live coverage and updates on the final.

name: Jimmy Carter
summary: Former President Jimmy Carter will turn 100 on October 1, and several events are planned to celebrate. The Carter Center will host "Jimmy Carter 100: A Celebration in Song" on September 17 at the Fox Theatre in Atlanta. Delta Air Lines is sponsoring the event. The concert will feature performances by artists including Trisha Yearwood, Amy Grant, and Vince Gill, and will be streamed live on CarterCenter.org. Carter recently announced that he is aiming to live long enough to vote for Kamala Harris in the 2024 presidential election. He said, "I'm trying to make it." Carter's grandson, Jason Carter, recently discussed the upcoming birthday on WTXL ABC 27 Tallahassee News. Vanity Fair reported that Carter is "trying to stay alive long enough to vote for Kamala Harris." FOX 5 Atlanta announced the "Jimmy Carter 100: A Celebration in Song" concert, and USA TODAY reported that Carter hopes to vote for Harris as his 100th birthday approaches. Atlanta Magazine also highlighted the upcoming tribute concert planned for Carter's 100th birthday, calling it "A Carter Centennial."
